The paper deals with the spread of influence in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of social networks (cs.SOC). The paper also introduces a new concept called AD-k, which is a generalization of monotonicity and submodularity, and applies it to the spread of influence. This makes it likely that the paper would also fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG).
